observations.recommendation:
1. Create the Inventory Committee of the municipality to conduct the inventory on the physical count of its road network and prepare a report thereon;
2. Require the Municipal Accountant to update the local roads network accounts based on the result of the physical count; and
3. Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Accountant and the General Services Office with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

18. Instruct the Municipal Accountant and other concerned officials in address and comply with the deficiencies noted during the validation and submit an updated copy of the same to the Auditor for review;
19. Moreover, require the same to strictly comply with the recording, updating, and maintaining of monthly accounting records, onwards;
20. Direct the same to conscientiously keep and file copies of the all the monthly reports submitted to the auditor.
